= Reliance upon Allāh (Tawakkul)


*Definition:*

 • Linguistically: Delegation and reliance.
 
 • In Islām: It is the heart’s reliance on Allāh alone and entrusting matters to Him.

== Shar‘i (Islamic) Tawakkul:

It involves three essential components:

- Sincere and genuine reliance on Allāh.
- Complete trust in Allāh and belief that all matters are in His control.
- Taking the permissible means and causes.


== Categories of Tawakkul:

 === 1. Tawakkul as Worship: 
 This is placing trust in Allāh alone, without any partner.
 
 === 2. Tawakkul that is Shirk:
- Relying on someone other than Allāh in what is exclusive to Allāh.
 
- Relying entirely or partially on worldly means, disregarding Allāh.

=== 3. Permissible Tawakkul:
Appointing someone to act on your behalf in matters they are capable of handling. this is called delegation.

== The Difference Between Tawakkul and Tawkīl:

 • Tawakkul is an internal, heartfelt act (a matter of the heart).
 
 • Tawkīl is an external, outward action (appointing someone to act on your behalf).


